# XVerse Remote Machines Configuration
# Format: user@hostname:port:remote_path
# 
# Examples:
# ubuntu@192.168.1.100:22:/home/ubuntu
# admin@server1.example.com:2222:/opt/cuttlefish
# user@10.0.0.50:22:/home/user/XVerse

# Add your remote machines below:
# ubuntu@192.168.1.100:22:/home/ubuntu
# ubuntu@192.168.1.101:22:/home/ubuntu
# ubuntu@192.168.1.102:22:/home/ubuntu

# Instructions:
# 1. Uncomment and modify the lines above with your actual remote machines
# 2. Ensure SSH key authentication is set up for passwordless access
# 3. Make sure the remote user has write permissions to the specified path
# 4. Run: ./deploy_cuttlefish.sh remotes.conf
